The paper deals with the problem of releasing private data while preserving differential privacy, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of privacy and security in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the problem of releasing the cut function of a graph, which is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves iterative constructions and algorithms, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the analysis of algorithms and the complexity of the problem, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
